### Obstacle System (Level 31+)

Obstacles are parked on the track at procedurally chosen positions along the centerline.

| Type | Visual | Effect | Density |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Pass-through** | Transparent ghost/coin ring, glowing cyan | No effect — cosmetic only (introduces players to obstacle positions) | High (3–5/lap) |
| **Slow-down** | Oil slick / mud puddle, flat disc, amber glow | Reduces car speed by 50% for 2 seconds | Medium (2–3/lap) |
| **Solid** | Orange barrel / concrete block, BoxGeometry | Collision → reduces car HP by 25, brief camera shake | Low (1–2/lap) |

**Car HP system:**
- Start with 100 HP
- HP bar shown in HUD (red/green gradient)
- HP regens 5/s when not hitting obstacles
- HP ≤ 0 → Game Over (car explosion particle burst)

**Obstacle spawning:**
```js
function spawnObstacles(curve, level) {
    if (level <= 30) return [];
    const count = Math.floor((level - 30) * 0.5) + 3;
    // Randomly pick t values along curve, avoid player start (t < 0.1)
    // Mix of 3 types weighted: 50% pass-through, 30% slow, 20% solid
}
```

**Obstacle collision:**
- Each frame compute distance from car's world position to each obstacle position
- Threshold: 2.5 units (half car width + half obstacle width)
- Apply effect based on obstacle type

